Subject: [bioinfo] SAVE THE DATE ! : SeMoVi Seminar, 28 January, 2 to 6 pm, Lyon

Dear all,
Save the date for the upcoming SeMoVi Seminar that will be held in Lyon on Tuesday, 28 January, from 2 to 6 pm !

We are pleased to welcome Pr Uwe SAUER (ETH, Zürich). His talk will bear on :
HOW MICROBES COORDINATE PATHWAY USAGE IN METABOLISM.

Uwe SAUER is a key player in the field of metabolic flux analysis.

Two talks from colleagues from Lyon and Grenoble will follow :
- Generating robust spatio-temporal patterns of morphogenesis in plants, by Teva VERNOUX, RDP Lab, Lyon
- Global regulation and the control of growth rate in Escherichia coli, by Hans GEISELMANN, LAPM Lab, Grenoble

This Seminar will take place at the 'Emilie du Chatelet' Conference Hall in the INSA Marie Curie Library, 31 avenue Jean Capelle Ouest, Villeurbanne. The nearest tram station is INSA-EINSTEIN, or LA DOUA/GASTON BERGER.

Share this information with your colleagues !

Best regards

